===罹患癌症的風險===
{{See also|Nuclear power debate#Health effects on population near nuclear power plants and workers}}
對於居住在鄰近核能設施的人來說,目前的流行病學研究指出已有各種疾病風險增加的趨勢,特別是癌症。一個2007年由貝克''et al.''所著17篇研究論文的[[元分析|元分析]]公布在歐洲癌症護理雜誌(''European Journal of Cancer Care'')<ref name="pmid17587361">{{cite journal|title=Meta-analysis of standardized incidence and mortality rates of childhood leukaemia in proximity to nuclear facilities|pages=355–363|issn=0961-5423|journal=European Journal of Cancer Care|volume=16|issue=4|date=2007-7|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2354.2007.00679.x|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17587361|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=P. J. Baker, D. G. Hoel|pmid=17587361|archive-date=2020-03-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200323175505/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/17587361|dead-url=no}}</ref>這份研究提供了關於居住在英國,加拿大,法國,美國,德國,日本和西班牙等地136個核能設施周邊兒童罹患血癌比率升高的證據。<ref name=mvr/> 然而這個研究受到了不同理由的批評-像是不同組成的資料(不同的年齡群,非核能發電場地,不同的區域定義),武斷的選取37之中的17份個別研究,將某些發電廠零觀察案例或死亡數排除在外等等。<ref>{{cite journal|title=Re: BAKER P.J. & HOEL D.G. (2007) European Journal of Cancer Care16, 355-363. Meta-analysis of standardized incidence and mortality rates of childhood leukaemia in proximity to nuclear facilities|pages=429–430|issn=1365-2354|journal=European Journal of Cancer Care|volume=18|issue=4|date=2009-7|doi=10.1111/j.1365-2354.2008.01027.x|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19594613|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Claudia Spix, Maria Blettner|pmid=19594613|archive-date=2019-09-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190916131246/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19594613|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name = COMARE/> 在2008年德國由Kaatsch ''et al.''所做的研究調查16個德國主要的核能發電廠周邊居民中發現了兒童罹患血癌比率的升高。<ref name="pmid17587361"/>這個研究也因為不同的原因而受到批評。<ref name = COMARE/><ref>{{cite journal|title=Leukaemia in young children living in the vicinity of nuclear power plants|pages=x–xi|issn=1097-0215|journal=International Journal of Cancer|volume=122|issue=4|date=2008-02-15|doi=10.1002/ijc.23347|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18072253|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Julian Little, John McLaughlin, Anthony Miller|pmid=18072253|archive-date=2019-09-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190914203012/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18072253|dead-url=no}}</ref>
已上這兩個研究結果與其他的研究相比是沒有前後一致的,別的研究都試圖不去凸顯這樣的關聯。 <ref name=mvr>[[M.V._Ramana|M.V. Ramana]]. Nuclear Power: Economic, Safety, Health, and Environmental Issues of Near-Term Technologies, ''Annual Review of Environment and Resources'', 2009. 34, p.142.</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Childhood leukaemia incidence below the age of 5 years near French nuclear power plants|pages=401–403|issn=0952-4746|journal=Journal of Radiological Protection: Official Journal of the Society for Radiological Protection|volume=28|issue=3|date=2008-9|doi=10.1088/0952-4746/28/3/N01|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18714138|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=D. Laurier, D. Hémon, J. Clavel|pmid=18714138|pmc=PMC2738848|archive-date=2019-09-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190923102727/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18714138|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>Lopez-Abente, Gonzalo et al, (2009)[http://scienzattiva2009.agorascienza.it/files/risposte/925.full.pdf Leukemia, Lymphomas, and Myeloma Mortality in the Vicinity of Nuclear Power Plants and Nuclear Fuel Facilities in Spain] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110826202756/http://scienzattiva2009.agorascienza.it/files/risposte/925.full.pdf |date=2011-08-26 }} Cancer Epidemiology, Biomarkers & Prevention, Vol. 8, 925–934, October 1999</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Cancer in populations living near nuclear facilities. A survey of mortality nationwide and incidence in two states|pages=1403–1408|issn=0098-7484|journal=JAMA|volume=265|issue=11|date=1991-03-20|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1999880|accessdate=2019-05-25|author=S. Jablon, Z. Hrubec, J. D. Boice|pmid=1999880|archive-date=2019-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915214321/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/1999880|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Research on potential radiation risks in areas with nuclear power plants in Japan: leukaemia and malignant lymphoma mortality between 1972 and 1997 in 100 selected municipalities|pages=343–368|issn=0952-4746|journal=Journal of Radiological Protection: Official Journal of the Society for Radiological Protection|volume=24|issue=4|date=2004-12|url=https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15682904|accessdate=2019-02-12|author=Yasuhiko Yoshimoto, Shinji Yoshinaga, Kazuhide Yamamoto, Kenzo Fijimoto, Kanae Nishizawa, Yasuhito Sasaki|pmid=15682904|archive-date=2019-09-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190915215308/https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/15682904|dead-url=no}}</ref>英國的醫學對環境輻射觀點委員會(The British Committee on Medical Aspects of Radiation in the Environment)在2011年發布了關於1969至2004年之間五歲以下兒童居住在13座英國核電廠周邊的研究。委員會發現在英國居住在核電廠周邊的孩童並不會比住在其他地方還要容易罹患血癌。<ref name = COMARE>Elliott, A, Editor (2011) [http://www.comare.org.uk/press_releases/documents/COMARE14report.pdf COMARE 14th Report: Further consideration of the incidence of childhood leukaemia around nuclear power plants in Great Britain] {{Wayback|url=http://www.comare.org.uk/press_releases/documents/COMARE14report.pdf |date=20130711063918 }} 6 May 2011, Retrieved 6 May 2011</ref>

===與火力發電比較===
就放射性的釋放淨值來說,美國放射線防護與測量會議(National Council on Radiation Protection and Measurements,NCRP)計算了每短噸煤炭的平均放射線為17,100毫居里/4,000,000噸。而美國國內154座燃煤火力發電廠,光是一座發電廠每年就會排放0.6319兆貝克的放射線。

就居住在附近的人口劑量而言,有時候這被拿來引證說燃煤電廠會釋放100倍的核電廠放射線量。這是來自於NCRP的第92和第95篇報告,報告中計算出1000百萬瓦特的煤和核能電力會分別讓人口受到4.9人-西弗([[集體劑量|集體劑量]])/年以及0.048人-西弗/年(比較上,一次典型的[[胸部X光|胸部X光]]劑量大約為0.06毫西弗)。<ref name=ornl>[http://www.ornl.gov/info/ornlreview/rev26-34/text/colmain.html Coal Combustion - ORNL Review Vol. 26, No. 3&4, 1993<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070205103749/http://www.ornl.gov/info/ornlreview/rev26-34/text/colmain.html |date=2007-02-05 }}</ref>[[美國國家環境保護局|美國國家環境保護局]]的計算中多增加了一些劑量:居住在距離燃煤電廠和核電廠80公里內每年放射線劑量分別為0.3微西弗和0.009毫侖目。<ref name=epac>The EPA. [http://www.epa.gov/radiation/understand/calculate.html Calculate Your Radiation Dose] {{Wayback|url=http://www.epa.gov/radiation/understand/calculate.html |date=20140531194411 }}</ref>核電廠在正常運作下排放的輻射量是少於燃煤電廠的。<ref name=ornl/><ref name=epac/>

不像燃煤發電或燃油發電,核能發電不會直接產生任何二氧化硫,氮氧化物或是汞(光是在美國,化石燃料造成的汙染就被批評使得每年有24,000人早死<ref name="catf-dada">{{Cite web|url=http://www.catf.us/publications/view/24|title=Dirty Air, Dirty Power: Mortality and Health Damage Due to Air Pollution from Power Plants|accessdate=2006-11-10|publisher=Clean Air Task Force|year=2004|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20060923055100/http://www.catf.us/publications/view/24|archive-date=2006-09-23|dead-url=yes}}</ref>)。然而,對所有的能源來講,總是會有像是採礦,生產與運輸等諸如此類的開發活動跟污染有所關聯。

一個由歐盟資助的學術性研究,ExternE(能源外部性,Externalities of Energy),跨越1995年到2005年之間進行研究發現核能發電所付出的環境與健康成本,每開發的能源單位為0.0019歐元/千瓦小時。這比很多將環境衝擊像是[[生物質|生物質]]利用和製作[[太陽能光電系統|太陽能光電系統]]納入其中去考量的[[再生能源|再生能源]]還低,並且是煤炭(0.06歐元/千瓦小時)影響的三十分之一還要更低。然而擁有最低的外部成本0.0009歐元/千瓦小時為[[風力發電|風力發電]],它的環境與健康影響大約為核能發電的一半。<ref>[http://www.externe.info/externe_2006/exterpols.html ExternE-Pol, External costs of current and advanced electricity systems, associated with emissions from the operation of power plants and with the rest of the energy chain, final technical report.] {{Wayback|url=http://www.externe.info/externe_2006/exterpols.html |date=20160415121518 }} See figure 9, 9b and figure 11</ref>

